[Teacher]: an exciting time for me because I was just starting to explore my interests and hobbies in college. I had been introduced to various groups and clubs, and I had even started taking classes to learn new skills. But as much as I was excited to learn new things, I was also struggling to find what really resonated with me.  It wasn't until I stumbled upon a photography club on campus that I felt a spark of excitement. I had always been interested in photography, but I never had the time to pursue it seriously. With the club, I could meet like-minded people, learn from their experiences, and practice my skills.  I have to say, I was hooked from the very first meeting. The sense of creativity and self-expression that came with photography was incredible. I loved the feeling of capturing a moment, of freezing time, and of sharing my vision with others.  But what keeps me interested is not just the technical aspects of photography. It's the way it allows me to see the world in a new light. It's the way it forces me to slow down and appreciate the beauty in everyday moments. It's the way it gives me a sense of purpose and fulfillment.  For me, photography is not just a hobby, but a way
